  <prompt>
    Filed 2026-05-26 as a follow-up to task 069 after the sub-agent fixed the originally-flagged
    7 errors and ~69 previously-MASKED pre-existing errors surfaced across ~17 other BFF test
    files. These were hidden because the build stopped early on the 7. Operator approved
    adding to R4 scope (2026-05-26) — "must ensure these issues are resolved as part of this
    project (Phase 6)".
  </prompt>

  <role>
    .NET 8 test-infrastructure engineer. The errors are mostly CS7036 (logger param additions
    in production handler ctors that weren't propagated to tests) + miscellaneous type drift.
    Fix in test files only — DO NOT modify production code.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` completes with 0 errors. `dotnet test` runs
    the full test suite end-to-end. R4-added tests (050 attachments, 053 ModifiedOn, 054 PUT+ETag)
    appear in the test run output and execute. No production code modified.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 069 sub-agent fixed 7 namespace-drift errors in 3 specific test files. After those
      fixes landed, the build advanced past the early-stop point and surfaced 69 additional
      pre-existing compile errors across ~17 other BFF test files. Sub-agent escalated per
      CLAUDE.md §6 (scope expansion).

      Per task 069 memo (`projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/test-infra-bff-handler-fix-2026-05-26.md`):
      - Dominant pattern: CS7036 (constructor missing required parameter — production handlers
        added `ILogger<T>` deps without updating test instantiations)
      - Secondary patterns: misc type drift from production refactors

      Per task 069 sub-agent's stash + rebuild verification on master baseline: ALL 69 errors
      are pre-existing — none introduced by R4 changes.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/test-infra-bff-handler-fix-2026-05-26.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">No production code modification. Fix in test files (or test helper files like fixtures, builders, mocks) only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If a production class genuinely cannot be tested due to a real design issue, ESCALATE per CLAUDE.md §6 — do NOT modify production code to "make tests pass".</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If a test is obsolete (tests a removed handler), DELETE it cleanly with a comment citing the removal commit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">If a handler test touches AI-internal types, route through `PublicContracts/` facade where possible.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">For CS7036 errors, the fix is to add the missing constructor param to the test instantiation (typically `Mock.Of<ILogger<T>>()` or `NullLogger<T>.Instance`).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/test-infra-bff-handler-fix-2026-05-26.md</file>
