      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Catalog">Run `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` and catalog all 69 errors: file + line + diagnostic ID + production class affected. Group by error pattern (CS7036 logger, CS0246 type missing, CS1503 type mismatch, etc.).</step>
    <step order="2" name="Triage by pattern">For each group, design the bulk fix pattern. E.g., for CS7036 logger: identify which production class added `ILogger<T>`; the standard fix is `new T(..., NullLogger<T>.Instance)` in tests OR `Mock.Of<ILogger<T>>()` if mock framework is used.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Apply bulk fixes">Apply the bulk fix patterns. Verify each group of fixes compiles before moving to the next.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Handle stragglers">Remaining one-off errors that don't fit a bulk pattern — fix individually. For obsolete tests (handler removed) — delete with comment.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify build">`dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` → 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify test run">`dotnet test` runs end-to-end. Capture: total tests, passed, failed. (Existing pre-existing failures are out of scope; just need the suite to execute.)</step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify R4 tests now run">Confirm R4-added tests are in the test run output: PUT+ETag (054), attachments (050), ModifiedOn wire-shape (053).</step>
    <step order="8" name="Document">Write `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/test-infra-bff-cascading-fix-2026-05-26.md` with: full 69-error catalog, fix patterns applied, file-by-file changes, current `dotnet test` baseline numbers.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Change task 070 status to ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Escalate (if applicable)">If any subset requires production-code change, ESCALATE before applying.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Inspect test files + production handlers (read-only)</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Fix test files</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run dotnet build + dotnet test</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Cross-reference production constructor signatures</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
